'''Thekkumbhagam''' ({{Lang-ml|<U+0D24><U+0D46><U+0D15><U+0D4D><U+0D15><U+0D41><U+0D02><U+0D2D><U+0D3E><U+0D17><U+0D02>}}) or '''Thekkumbhagom''' is the southern border town of [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur municipality]] in the [[Kollam district]] of [[Kerala]], [[India]].  It is located at the Southern tip of [[Kollam district|Kollam's]] coastal area. It is in the [[Arabian Sea]] coast<ref>[http://www.getpincode.info/thekkumbhagam-paravoor-kollam Paravur Thekkumbhagam]</ref>. Thekkumbhagam-[[Kappil,_Thiruvananthapuram|Kappil]] estuary point in the [[Kollam]]-[[Thiruvananthapuram]] coastal border is on of the emerging tourism spots in the state.<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-in-school/beach-and-backwaters-beckon-discerning-tourists-at-kappil/article4902997.ece Beach and backwaters beckon discerning tourists at Kappil]</ref> On 1936, during formation, Thekkumbhagam was one of the 9 territories of [[Paravur, Kollam|Paravur]] Panchayath<ref>[http://paravoorsouth.blogspot.in/p/history.html History of Paravur]</ref>. The place is very famous for its natural beauty.

== Notable people ==

* Dr. K.M Bahauddin, Ex. Pro-Vice Chancellor of Annamalai University<ref>[http://www.milligazette.com/news/966-obituaries-indian-muslims Obituaries - Dr. K.M Bahauddin]</ref>

